<div class="main large"><h3>Button Groups</h3>
  <p>
  Use the mixin <i>btn-group()</i> for button groups. Use the <i>data-toggle="buttons"</i> attribute to enable radio button like behaviour. Use the <i>data-toggle="button"</i> attribute to enable checkbox like behaviour.
  <br><br>

  To use the mixin in CSS:
  <br><br>
  </p>

<code><pre>
.btn-group { 
  @include btn-group(); 
}

...

&lt;div class="btn-group" data-toggle="buttons"&gt;
  &lt;a class="btn"&gt;Button One&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;a class="btn"&gt;Button Two&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;a class="btn"&gt;Button Three&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</pre></code>
<br><br>

<p>
With <i>data-toggle="buttons"</i> attribute:
<br>
<div class="btn-group" data-toggle="buttons">
  <a class="btn">Choice 1</a>
  <a class="btn">Choice 2</a>
  <a class="btn">Choice 3</a>
</div><br>
<div class="btn-group" data-toggle="buttons">
  <a class="btn">Choice 1</a>
  <a class="btn">Choice 2</a>
</div><br>
<div class="btn-group" data-toggle="buttons">
  <a class="btn">Choice 1</a>
</div>
<br><br>

With <i>data-toggle="button"</i> attribute:
<br>
<div class="btn-group" data-toggle="button">
  <a class="btn" color="raised1">1</a>
  <a class="btn" color="raised1">2</a>
  <a class="btn" color="raised1">3</a>
</div><br>
<div class="btn-group" data-toggle="button">
  <a class="btn" color="raised1">1</a>
  <a class="btn" color="raised1">2</a>
</div><br>
<div class="btn-group" data-toggle="button">
  <a class="btn" color="raised1">1</a>
</div></div>

